arch:property.oc:show_val: This is from the floor/occupation surface in space 89, below the burnt layer. Sample 1 >4 mm flotation 100% sorted, recorded completely. Largish sample for floor unit. Range of fragment sizes from tiny up to 6 cm. Mostly sheep-size, a little large mammal, mostly scapula fragments. Even body part distribution, including some horn core and antler bits. Burnt tip of bone point. Fair amount of burning, rather weathered, some digestion. No sense of integrity. Seems more like fill than floor. Last number = 59 LY 2001: Extra data added when a further bag of dry sieve material was recorded. First record starts at F60 as the rest of the data is on the master copy recorded in previous years.
